    • Class group10.server.entity.EntityBase extends Object implements Serializable

      • Serialized Fields

        • active
          boolean active
          Boolean field to state if the entry is soft-deleted or not.
        • createDate
          Date createDate
          Create date for the entry.
        • id
          long id
          Primary Key that is automatically incremented by every insert.
        • operationType
          String operationType
          Field that stores the operation type for the most recent operation that has happened. Can be either save, update or delete.

          Date updateDate
          Update date for the entry.

    • Class group10.server.entity.Match extends EntityBase implements Serializable

      • Serialized Fields

        • game
          Game game
          Field for storing Game information. Since a Game has multiple matches due to multiple levels, the relation is ManyToOne.
        • level
          int level
          Field for storing the Match level.
        • player
          Player player
          Field for storing Player information. Since a Player has multiple matches due to multiple levels and games, the relation is ManyToOne.
        • score
          int score
          Field for storing score value.

    • Class group10.server.entity.PendingPwCode extends EntityBase implements Serializable

      • Serialized Fields

        • code
          String code
          Field that stores the password reset code.
        • player
          Player player
          Field for storing Player information. Since a Player can have multiple password reset requests the relation is ManyToOne.

    • Class group10.server.entity.Player extends EntityBase implements Serializable

      • Serialized Fields

        • email
          String email
          Field for storing email. Must be unique.
        • password
          String password
          Field for storing password. Ignored in JSON responses to keep passwords hashes safe.
        • roles
          List<Role> roles
          Relation for storing Role information. Since a user can have many roles, and since roles can belong to multiple users, the relation is ManyToMany.
        • username
          String username
          Field for storing username. Must be unique.

      • Serialized Fields
